radiographic_examinations.findings: The visualized lung base showed minimal dependent atelectasis. The appendix is visualized and measures up to 15 mm in diameter, is hyperenhancing, and has extensive inflammation surrounding it. Scattered mesenteric lymph nodes are seen. There is no organized fluid collection or free air. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys, bladder, prostate, and rectum appear unremarkable.
